710459f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 14th Street (West)
710459f-a.text:
(1)
Tenth Ave., (right), north from and including West 14th Street, showing the National Biscuit Co. plant at West 15th extending to 16th Streets, and also facing on Eleventh Ave. (left). two bridges connect the main plant, with a new annex; through which pass the elevated tracks of the N.Y. Central R.R. Also shown (left), is a portion of the elevated West Side Vehicular Pighway, running north on Eleventh Ave.
March 31, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing a view slightly eastward.
March 31, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

710460f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 14th Street
710460f-b.text:
(1)
Tenth Avenue, east side, north from 14th Street. The front of the National Biscuit Company Building has been demolished for the construction of the elevated trestle of the New York
Central railroad.
March 16, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same.
September 6, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same. A filling station now occupies the N.E. corner of 14th Street, the New York Central elevated trestle has been erected, and the National Biscuit Company has extended the front of its building to Tenth Avenue, to replace that part of the old building which was demolished for the railroad
structure.
June 20, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
